  "title": "Vectors in one dimension - velocity comparison",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures, labeled A and B, are shown. Each figure shows two velocity vectors. In Figure A, one short vector points horizontally to the left and is labeled 5 meters per second, and one long vector points horizontally to the right and is labeled 10 meters per second. In Figure B, one short vector points horizontally to the right and is labeled 5 meters per second, and one long vector points horizontally to the left and is labeled 10 meters per second.\" src=\"/images/eae59da5c1e80866aa29286a371519da.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Figure A and Figure B both show two velocity vectors. Let <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector A\"><math alttext=\"vector A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector B\"><math alttext=\"vector B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span></span> be the vector sums of the velocity vectors in Figure A and Figure B, respectively. Are the speed and the velocity of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector A\"><math alttext=\"vector A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span></span> the same as the speed and velocity of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector B\"><math alttext=\"vector B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Yes, because both vectors have the same magnitude.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Yes, because both vectors point in the same direction.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">No, because <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector A\"><math alttext=\"vector A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span></span> has a magnitude of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 5 meters per second\"><math alttext=\"positive 5 meters per second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m/s</mtext></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector B\"><math alttext=\"vector B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span></span> has a magnitude of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative 5 meters per second\"><math alttext=\"negative 5 meters per second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m/s</mtext></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">No, because the vectors are in opposite directions, which means the velocities are different.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
